## Using AI Assistants (optional)

This vault includes a `.claude/` scaffold that teaches AI coding agents how to work with your world.

To use it, open the vault directory in an AI coding agent such as [Claude Code](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code), Codex, or OpenCode. The agent automatically picks up:

- **Skills** in `.claude/skills/` — Obsidian conventions, Grimoire's three-layer model, and your project-specific canon rules
- **Commands** in `.claude/commands/` — worldbuilding workflows you can run
{% if include_sources %}
### Ingesting source material

If you're adapting from existing source material, the `/ingest-source` command can help. It reads a chapter, wiki page, or reference text and extracts structured entity notes into `world/` with proper frontmatter and wikilinks. Run it from your AI coding agent:

```
/ingest-source
```

You can also ingest source material manually: create notes in `sources/` for raw material, then create entity notes in `world/` using the templates.
